Forth the Volseians speed in even line, driving on their tortoise-shield, and intent to fill the moat and pluek down the palisade. Some seek entrance, and essay to scale the walls with ladders, where the line is thin, and light gleams through the less dense ring of men. In return, the Teucrians shower missiles of every sort, and thrust the foe down with strong poles, trained by long warfare to defend their walls.
